<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS FULLER RT-610 SERIES - REMOVE - LOW SPEED GEAR AND OUTPUT SHAFT ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="2">
        <title>LOW SPEED GEAR AND OUTPUT SHAFT ASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Drive or press against the rear of the output shaft to move the assembly forward and from
                the rear bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302456">Figure 56</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302456" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302456" filename="../figg13/G1302456.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 56. Move Assembly Forward and From Rear Bearing</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the rear washer and the low speed gear from the rear of the shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302457">Figure 57</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302457" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302457" filename="../figg13/G1302457.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 57. Remove Rear Washer and Low Speed Gear</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the spline washer from the hub of the low speed gear.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Move the mainshaft rear bearing to the rear and out of the housing.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a bearing driver to remove the countershaft rear bearings from the housing.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
